				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "# Board Elements — Composition over Inheritance"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"createTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-04-06T20:28:24.035963-04:00"
					}
				},
				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-04-06T20:28:24.035963-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "WiRvMligSRq+SEUNxo2Wkw=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "The kanban board UI uses **composition** rather than inheritance. There are three element classes:\n\n**{{gtClass:GtEnsembleBoardElement}}** — a pure kanban layout engine (subclass of `BrHorizontalPane`). Groups items by a bucket block, renders columns with drag-and-drop. Knows nothing about projects or tasks — it just takes a collection, a grouping function, and a group class.\n\n**{{gtClass:GtEnsembleProjectBoardElement}}** — composes a `GtEnsembleBoardElement` with a project-specific toolbar containing an \"Add project\" button and {{gtClass:GtEnsembleProjectForm}}.\n\n**{{gtClass:GtEnsembleTaskBoardElement}}** — composes a `GtEnsembleBoardElement` with a task-specific toolbar containing an \"Add task\" button and {{gtClass:GtEnsembleTaskForm}}. Accepts an optional project for scoping: when scoped, the form pre-fills the project; when unscoped (all tasks), the form shows a project picker.\n\nThis design was chosen because:\n- The board element is a **reusable layout widget**, not a domain concept — subclassing it per type would couple layout to domain logic\n- Each context (home card, inspector view, Lepiter snippet) can wrap the same board with different chrome\n- Adding a new board type (e.g., by-tag board) only requires a new wrapper, not a new base class"
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
				"children" : {
					"__type" : "snippets",
					"items" : [ ]
				},
				"createEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
