				"editEmail" : {
					"__type" : "email",
					"emailString" : "<unknown>"
				},
				"editTime" : {
					"__type" : "time",
					"time" : {
						"__type" : "dateAndTime",
						"dateAndTimeString" : "2026-04-06T20:29:44.507434-04:00"
					}
				},
				"uid" : {
					"__type" : "uid",
					"uidString" : "lpI59VWbQjqrdCYOjW7sNA=="
				},
				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "Ensemble is **not coupled to a single Lepiter database**. {{gtMethod:GtEnsembleBoard>>#loadFromLepiter}} scans all loaded databases for pages containing ensemble snippets. Any page in any database that contains a {{gtClass:GtEnsembleProjectSnippet}} or {{gtClass:GtEnsembleTaskSnippet}} is automatically discovered.\n\nWhen creating a new project, the {{gtClass:GtEnsembleProjectForm}} includes a database picker (defaulting to the first loaded database). Once created, the project's database association is implicit — the page lives in the database, and the project links to the page.\n\nThis means users can keep their project pages in their own personal Lepiter database rather than in the gt4ensemble repository database. The gt4ensemble database should contain only documentation and example pages."
			},
			{
				"__type" : "textSnippet",
